casebody.data:
James M. Constable et al., Respondents, v. Samuel Corn, et al., Appellants. Decided March 14, 1887. Appeal by defendants from judgment entered upon verdict óf jury, and from order denying motion for new trial made upon judge’s minutes. A. E. Dyett, for appellants. B. F. Watson, for respondents.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Freedman, J.

Per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
